                  </hi> I live at 13, Lewisham Place, Lewisham—on the evening of the 8th July I was in the prosecutrix's (my sister's) shop, which is next door—I had occasion to go into me own shop, and when I returned I saw the prisoner outside with something under his arm—I said to him, "I want you, "and he ran away, and I after him—he dropped the boots and was stopped by another—the boots were hanging up on a shelf on the right-hand side of the door—they are my sister's property.</p>
